-# What the cavity simulation computes
-
-For a given geometry the code computes:
+## What The Model Includes
 
-- Stability maps (|m| < 1)
-- Eigenmodes via the round-trip ABCD matrix
-- Beam waist maps
-- Single-point evaluation:
-  - q-parameters
-  - waist in the crystal
-  - round-trip lengths (geometric and optical)
+- Paraxial cavity analysis from ABCD matrices
+- Reflectivity-based cavity loss modeling
+- Temperature-dependent crystal refractive-index and phase-matching calculations
+- Focused-beam mode matching and Boyd-Kleinman analysis
+- A compact degenerate below-threshold OPO model
+- A minimal 2x2 quadrature-basis Langevin/squeezing workflow
 
-Derived quantities:
+## What The Model Does Not Include
 
-- Free Spectral Range (FSR)
-- decay rates: `kappa_ext`, `kappa_loss`, `kappa_total`
-- escape efficiency and detuning
-- Gouy phases
+- Full non-degenerate multimode OPO dynamics
+- Full first-principles threshold derivation
+- Automatic cavity-geometry retuning when the crystal operating point changes
+- Thermal, photothermal, or pump-depletion dynamics beyond the current compact model
 
-These quantities are the required inputs for later simulations of:
+## Repository Layout
 
-- nonlinear gain
-- OPO threshold
-- squeezing spectra
